(thirdQuint)Evaluation of Acclimate Feature for Positive Airway Pressure (PAP) Therapy.

 Acclimate has been designed as a comfort feature for patients starting PAP therapy.

 The feature allows acclimatization to the targeted positive airway pressure setting.

 Using the Acclimate feature, the pressure increases incrementally over a period of time.

 The feature can be only be used for a set period of time, afterwards which the device initiates the therapeutic session at the prescribed pressure.

